    <string name="about_title">About Ringdroid</string>
    <string name="about_text"><![CDATA[Use Ringdroid to edit MP3, WAV, and AMR audio files and create ringtones, alarms, and notifications from them.\n\nTip: copy audio files to your SD card using a USB cable, or get MP3s using the Amazon MP3 application.\n\nTip: tap anywhere on the waveform to start playing at that position.  More below...\n\nTip: while playing, tap the word Start or End to quickly set the start and end markers to the current playback time.\n\nTip: Use the jog wheel for more precise adjustments.\n\nDeveloper: Dominic Mazzoni\nGraphics: Joseph Wain\nSupport: Eugene Koh\n\nRingdroid is free software, distributed under the Apache 2.0 license.  Source code is on code.google.com\n]]></string>

